    <briefdescription>
<para>Multi-Class Slab Memory Allocator. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Partitions a single caller-provided static memory pool into multiple fixed-size slab block classes (e.g. 16B, 64B, 256B). Allocations and frees execute in deterministic O(1) time without heap fragmentation. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
